#MEM id=security-test-checklist source=/root/yvon/agent-department/Technical/quinn/skills/custom/security-test-checklist/SKILL.md
M|security-test-checklist|name: sec-test-checklist
M|security-test-checklist|description: Quinn's sec gate checklist — runs before issuing any ap verdict. Covers auth bypass, cross-vtr isolation, rate limiting, client bundle key scan, XSS, RLS spot-check, and CORS verification
M|security-test-checklist|version: 1.0.0
M|security-test-checklist|A feature that passes functional QA but has a sec hole is not ready to ship. Quinn is the last gate before Dev merges — which means Quinn is also the last check that catches sec failures before they r
M|security-test-checklist|Run all items. Check "N/A" only if the item genuinely doesn't apply to this feature (e.g., no auth routes = auth tests N/A). Never skip without stating why.
M|security-test-checklist|- [ ] **Unauthenticated access** — Send an unauthenticated request to every protected endpoint this feature uses. Expected: `401`. Actual: ___
M|security-test-checklist|- [ ] **Expired ses** — Use an expired or invalid token. Expected: `401` with clear message. Actual: ___
M|security-test-checklist|- [ ] **Invalid token** — Use a malformed JWT. Expected: `401`. Actual: ___
M|security-test-checklist|- [ ] **Auth failure rsp** — Confirm the 401 body contains only a generic message. No stack trace, no route name, no DB schema info.
M|security-test-checklist|- [ ] **vtr A → vtr B data** — Authenticate as a Novizio user; attempt to access Hourbour-specific data (change the `yvon_active_venture` cookie or `x-vtr-slug` header). Expected: `403` or data scoped
M|security-test-checklist|- [ ] **Cookie tampering** — Manually change the `yvon_active_venture` cookie value to another vtr slug. Expected: data remains scoped to the authenticated vtr, not the tampered cookie value.
M|security-test-checklist|- [ ] **AI route threshold** — Send > 20 requests in 60 seconds to any AI endpoint this feature uses. Expected: `429` status with `Retry-After` header.
M|security-test-checklist|- [ ] **Rate limit rsp body** — Confirm the 429 body contains a user-safe message only. No internal route structure exposed.
M|security-test-checklist|- [ ] **Retry-After header present** — Confirm `Retry-After` header is included in the 429 rsp.
M|security-test-checklist|- [ ] **API key scan** — After `npm run build`, search the `.next/static` output for any private API key strings (Anthropic, Apify, YouTube, Supabase service role). Expected: zero results.
M|security-test-checklist|```bash
M|security-test-checklist|grep -r "ANTHROPIC\|APIFY\|SERVICE_ROLE" .next/static/ 2>/dev/null
M|security-test-checklist|```
M|security-test-checklist|- [ ] **NEXT_PUBLIC_ audit** — rv all `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` vars in `.env.local`. Confirm none contain secrets, API keys, or credentials.
M|security-test-checklist|- [ ] **Script injection** — Submit `<script>alert('xss')</script>` in every user-input field this feature exposes. Expected: script does not execute in the browser; cnt is rendered as text or rejecte
M|security-test-checklist|- [ ] **Event handler injection** — Submit `"><img src=x onerror=alert(1)>` in text inputs. Expected: no alert, cnt rendered safely.
M|security-test-checklist|- [ ] **SQL injection string** — Submit `'; DROP TABLE users; --` in any search or filter field. Expected: safe error rsp, no crash, no DB error exposed to client.
M|security-test-checklist|- [ ] **Anonymous DB access** — If this feature introduced a new Supabase table or query, test accessing it without auth. Expected: blocked by RLS policy, zero rows returned.
M|security-test-checklist|- [ ] **Wrong vtr access** — Test querying the new table with a different venture_slug. Expected: zero rows returned (RLS scoping enforced).
M|security-test-checklist|- [ ] **CORS headers** — Check the `Access-Control-Allow-Origin` header on all API endpoints this feature introduces or modifies. Expected: no `*` on authenticated endpoints; origin scoped to YVON's d
M|security-test-checklist|- [ ] **Load `skills/custom/error-log-audit/SKILL.md`** and run its checklist against this feature's API routes.
M|security-test-checklist|If ANY item fails (not N/A) → **BLOCKED**. doc exactly which test failed, what was expected, and what was returned.
M|security-test-checklist|```
M|security-test-checklist|sec test result: PASSED / FAILED
M|security-test-checklist|Failed items:
M|security-test-checklist|- [test name]: expected [X], got [Y]
M|security-test-checklist|Fix required: [specific change needed in which file]
M|security-test-checklist|```
M|security-test-checklist|Three or more sec failures on the same feature → flag to Dev as a pattern issue, not just a bug list.